text: Barbora Blažková (born 23 September 1997) is a Czech ski jumper.. Retrieved 1 March 2018. She has competed at World Cup level since the 2012/13 season, with her best individual result being 23rd place in Oberstdorf on 8 January 2017. At the 2013 European Youth Olympic Winter Festival, she won a mixed team gold medal. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Czech female ski jumpers Category:People from Jablonec nad Nisou
